"NT Run for Life”
4 Jun 2023

Activity "NT Run for Life”

NAT Absolute Technologies PCL is proud to be a part of the charitable donation initiative in support of National Telecom Public Company Limited. Our company is committed to supporting the "NT Run for Life" charity event, which took place on Sunday, June 4th, 2566. The main objective of this collaboration is to foster a strong relationship between National Telecom Public Company Limited and its customers, as well as the public who participated in the event.

The proceeds from this initiative, after deducting expenses, were used to purchase medical equipment for donation to Wangyang Hospital, Nathom Hospital, Wangyang Wittayakom School, and Nathom Wittaya School in Nakhon Phanom province.


            

            


The Strengthening the Nation's Future Project
We believe that investing in education is a key to creating a better world for everyone. NATAT Absolute Technologies Public Company Limited organized a project to support the children of the Baan Dek Sanrak Kindergarten under the Foundation for Children
More details
LET'S SAVE THE EARTH
NAT Absolute Technologies Public Company Limited, has initiated a project to advocate for employees' environmental consciousness regarding emission reduction into the environment. The goal is to encourage employees to be mindful of the environment, starting with simple adjustments in behavior to reduce greenhouse gas emissions from various organizational activities. Our aspiration is to actively contribute to mitigating global warming for the sake of future generations.
More details
Project: Plastic Bottle Caps Initiative
We kindly present the Plastic Bottle Caps Initiative! Project, This initiative aims to deliver plastic bottle caps to support the "Precious Plastic Bangkok" project. Our goal is to contribute to organizations that recycle plastic bottle caps, in order to reduce waste and protect our planet.
More details
FEED X MATICHON TV GOLF CHARITY 2022
NAT Absolute Technologies PCL (formerly known as NAT Consulting Co., Ltd.) proudly participated in the FEED X MATICHON TV GOLF CHARITY 2022 event on December 14, 2565. As part of our commitment to social responsibility, a portion of the proceeds, after deducting expenses, was donated to the Mirror Foundation - Home for Disabled Animals.
